                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1868: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-09T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 9, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4165. Your 4286, June 29, 11 p.m. In as much as it was contemplated that the
                    matter dealt with in the Department’s 3586, June 9, 7 p.m., was to have been
                    considered by the War Cabinet on July 1st, it would be appreciated if the
                    Department might be furnished with a reply as soon as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
